AB  - This note is intended to demonstrate the robustness of the exponential assumption regarding depreciation in the Solow neoclassical one sector model of economic growth. Specifically, we shall show that for virtually any pattern of depreciation, there exists an average depreciation rate that replaces the exponential one in the stationary state equation and, for the usual neoclassical version of the production function, the capital-labor ratio converges to a steady state.
